Package neureka.devices.opencl

Class OpenCLDevice

java.lang.Object
neureka.devices.AbstractBaseDevice<V>
neureka.devices.AbstractDevice<Number>
neureka.devices.opencl.OpenCLDevice
All Implemented Interfaces:
Component<Tensor<Number>>, Device<Number>, Storage<Number>
public class OpenCLDevice extends AbstractDevice<Number>
This class models OpenCL supporting accelerator hardware like GPUs or FPGAs for storing tensors and executing operations on them.

    • compileAndGetAdHocKernel

      public KernelCaller compileAndGetAdHocKernel(String name, String source)
      This method compiles and returns the KernelCaller for a so called "ad hoc" kernel. Ad hoc is a Latin phrase meaning literally 'to this'. In English, it generally signifies a solution designed for a specific problem or task, non-generalizable, and not intended to be adapted to other purposes. This leads to the purpose of ad hoc kernel compilation, namely to be able to compile unique kernels with a specific purpose created on the fly during runtime by operations. This might be useful for high performance operations on tensors with specific dimensions and or possibly other variables / properties which might be taken into account...
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the kernel which ought to be compiled.
      source - The source of the kernel which ought to be compiled.
      Returns:
      The KernelCaller for the compiled kernel.

      This method compiles so called "ad hoc" kernel. Ad hoc is a Latin phrase meaning literally 'to this'. In English, it generally signifies a solution designed for a specific problem or task, non-generalizable, and not intended to be adapted to other purposes. This leads to the purpose of ad hoc kernel compilation, namely to be able to compile unique kernels with a specific purpose created on the fly during runtime by operations. This might be useful for high performance operations on tensors with specific dimensions and or possibly other variables / properties which might be taken into account...
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the kernel which ought to be compiled.

      Returns:

    • optimizedOperationOf

      public Operation optimizedOperationOf(Function function, String name)
      Description copied from interface: Device
      This method tries to allow this device to produce an optimized Operation based on the provided function. This is especially useful in an OpenCL context which can compile the function into native GPU kernels at runtime.
      Parameters:
      function - The function which should be turned into an optimized operation.
      name - The name of the returned operation.
      Returns:
      An optimized operation based on the provided function, or null if optimization is not possible.

    • restore

      public Device<Number> restore(Tensor<Number> tensor)
      This method assumes that the passed tensor is stored on this device instance. If the tensor is stored on the device then the method loads the outsourced data of the tensor back into primitive JVM arrays and restores the tensor freshly in RAM.
      Parameters:
      tensor - The tensor whose data ought to be restored (loaded to RAM).
      Returns:
      This device, which enables method chaining.
